I just gotta say this random thing.
People try to motivate people to start exercising by talking about how all you have to do is go run 5 miles in the morning, 5 miles at night, but that's more of an end goal or a starting goal in an anime.
Go for a WALK, not a run, for ONE hour each day (and personally I sorta just got into walking by doing it whenever there was an event in Pokemon Go). If you do a 10 minute walk you might not see yourself get exhausted, so you need for it to go longer. If you ran that distance with almost zero experience in fitness you will tire out and not get exhausted long term, and give up.

I can never just go outside and have fun, I need to do something to entertain myself personally so maybe walk with a friend if you have one IRL, or call a friend that you might have online and chat while walking.
